        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 2 at 3:43PM CDT until May 2 at 4:15PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Columbus,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters have reported quarter-size hail.
Multiple reports of a non-rotating wall cloud have been
received.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Columbus and Eagle Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
